1. **`encode_varint`**: Takes an integer value and encodes it using varint encoding. It extracts 7 bits at a time from the value, sets the continuation bit (MSB) for all but the last byte, and writes each byte to the stream.

2. **`decode_varint`**: Reads bytes from the stream, extracting the 7 data bits from each byte and reconstructing the original value. It continues reading until it encounters a byte without the continuation bit set.

3. **`encode_decode_roundtrip`**: Tests the correctness by encoding a value into a buffer, then decoding it from the same buffer, and comparing the result with the original value.

